note.#text:
The reference is to Socrates. Cicero often quotes this
oracle:  2. 10;  4. 13;  21. 78; 
i. 4. 16.

This was the traditional but unjust view held by the
Romans.  Livy xxi. 4. 9: Hor.  iii. 6. 361; 
iv. 4. 42; Juv. vii. 161.

According to the Stoics the wise man needed nothing,
though there were many things advisable for him to have;
cf. Seneca,  Plato,  B.
